{"title":"Autocursing/ko","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Autocursing/ko","type":"markdown","data":"Certain nasty items will **autocurse** themselves (that is, instantly become [cursed](/wiki/Cursed \"Cursed\")), so exercise caution even if an item does not appear to be cursed. 축복받은 물건도 초반 플레이어가 의심하는 것처럼 단순히 저주받은것이 아닌 것도 저주가 된다는 점을 강조해야 합니다. The only items that autocurse are:\n\n- [Loadstones](/wiki/Loadstone \"Loadstone\") (appearance: 회색 돌)\n- [Helms of opposite alignment](/wiki/Helm_of_opposite_alignment \"Helm of opposite alignment\") ([randomized appearance](/wiki/Randomized_appearance \"Randomized appearance\"))\n- [Dunce caps](/wiki/Dunce_cap \"Dunce cap\") (appearance: [원뿔 모자](/wiki/Conical_hat \"Conical hat\"))\n\nThe helm and the dunce cap will become cursed when [worn](/wiki/Wear \"Wear\") by a player, while the loadstone only becomes cursed when dropped - that is, picking up an uncursed loadstone is perfectly safe. However, since all loadstones are generated cursed (except possibly those in containers), they are still best left alone. 만약 당신이 [wizard](/wiki/Wizard \"Wizard\"), you can safely ignore all conical hats, since the only other hat that shares that appearance is the [cornuthaum](/wiki/Cornuthaum \"Cornuthaum\"), which is only beneficial to [wizards](/wiki/Wizard \"Wizard\") or to give [large](/wiki/Large \"Large\")-sized [pets](/wiki/Pet \"Pet\") [magic cancellation](/wiki/Magic_cancellation \"Magic cancellation\").\n\n## 더 보기\n\n- [scroll of scare monster](/wiki/Scroll_of_scare_monster \"Scroll of scare monster\"), which also changes [beatitude](/wiki/Beatitude \"Beatitude\") when dropped by players\n\n[![This article may require revision for the next version of NetHack. Click here for more information.](/images/b/b0/Nh343-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article may require revision for the next version of NetHack. Click here for more information.\")\n\n**This page may need to be updated for the [current version](/wiki/Current_version \"Current version\") of *NetHack*.**\n\nIt may contain text specific to [NetHack 3.4.3](/wiki/NetHack_3.4.3 \"NetHack 3.4.3\"). Information on this page may be out of date.\n\n**Editors:** After reviewing this page and making necessary edits, please change the {{nethack-343}} tag to the current version's tag or {{noversion}} as appropriate.\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Autocursing/ko - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Autocursing/ko\",\"wgTitle\":\"Autocursing/ko\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":135087,\"wgRevisionId\":135087,\"wgArticleId\":37113,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Item attributes\",\"Nethack-343 articles\",\"한국어\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",\"April\",\"May\",\"June\",\"July\",\"August\",\"September\",\"October\",\"November\",\"December\"],\"wgMonthNamesShort\":[\"\",\"Jan\",\"Feb\",\"Mar\",\"Apr\",\"May\",\"Jun\",\"Jul\",\"Aug\",\"Sep\",\"Oct\",\"Nov\",\"Dec\"],\"wgRelevantPageName\":\"Autocursing/ko\",\"wgRelevantArticleId\":37113,\"wgRequestId\":\"9bd45e6b7d9d17ba2e8d3219\",\"wgCSPNonce\":false,\"wgIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRelevantPageIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRestrictionEdit\":[],\"wgRestrictionMove\":[],\"wgWikiEditorEnabledModules\":[],\"wgCategoryTreePageCategoryOptions\":\"{\\\"mode\\\":0,\\\"hideprefix\